DocPad is a language agnostic document management system. This means you write your website as documents, in whatever language you wish, and DocPad will handle the compiling, templates and layouts for you. For static documents it will generate static files, for dynamic documents it'll re-render them on each request. You can utilise DocPad by itself, or use it as a module your own custom system. It's pretty cool, and well worth checking out. We love it.

JSDev is a filter that activates selected comments, making them executable.

This is a wrapper for use JSDev in your node project.  It will change hte require function behavior.  Check the project homepage on github to learn more.

If you just want to use JSDev, check the `JSDev` module(it's another module since npm registry is case-sensitive).

JSDev is a simple JavaScript preprocessor. It implements a tiny macro language that is written in the form of tagged comments. These comments are normally ignored, and will be removed by JSMin. But JSDev will activate these comments, replacing them with executable forms that can be used to do debugging, testing, logging, or tracing. JSDev scans a source looking for and replacing patterns. A pattern is a slashstar comment containing a tag and some stuff, and optionally a condition wrapped in parens. There must be no space between the slashstar and the <tag>.
